1
00:00:00,600 --> 00:00:04,590
[Never Too Late]

2
00:00:05,727 --> 00:00:09,687
[Episode 9]

3
00:00:25,479 --> 00:00:28,140
This kid is not answering the phone again.

4
00:00:28,700 --> 00:00:33,380
Senyun, did Xiao Ran say when they would be back?

5
00:00:33,380 --> 00:00:35,404
No.

6
00:00:38,140 --> 00:00:40,619
I'm going back to get some fruits to eat.

7
00:00:40,619 --> 00:00:42,859
No, no.

8
00:00:43,419 --> 00:00:46,020
Baobei, do you want fruits?

9
00:00:46,020 --> 00:00:48,799
I bought some grapes this morning. I'll get them for you.

10
00:00:49,600 --> 00:00:52,740
But I don't want to eat grapes. I want to eat peaches.

11
00:00:52,740 --> 00:00:56,120
There are also peaches. I'll get them for you. Sit down.

12
00:00:57,919 --> 00:01:01,839
I'll go back and get some honey lemon tea. We can add some water and drink it.

13
00:01:01,839 --> 00:01:05,359
No, Baobei. Well…

14
00:01:05,359 --> 00:01:09,199
Director Wang gave me some new tea yesterday. Shall we drink tea?

15
00:01:09,892 --> 00:01:10,940
Sure.

16
00:01:10,940 --> 00:01:12,799
Wait a moment.

17
00:01:18,919 --> 00:01:20,140
Baobei.

18
00:01:20,140 --> 00:01:22,019
Baobei, what are you doing?

19
00:01:25,059 --> 00:01:27,236
- There is something wrong with you.
- No.

20
00:01:27,236 --> 00:01:29,919
- You're hiding something from me.
- No.

21
00:01:29,919 --> 00:01:32,580
- Are you going to say it or not?
- Really nothing.

22
00:01:32,580 --> 00:01:35,479
- You definitely have something to hide from me.
- Really not.

23
00:01:35,479 --> 00:01:37,460
Are you going to say it or not?

24
00:01:38,640 --> 00:01:41,220
Mom, I'm back.

25
00:01:41,220 --> 00:01:43,460
Baby, you're back.

26
00:01:43,460 --> 00:01:46,180
I missed you so much.

27
00:01:46,180 --> 00:01:50,240
Xile just sent me a message. She said she wanted to give you a surprise.

28
00:01:50,240 --> 00:01:52,139
Let me look at you.

29
00:01:52,139 --> 00:01:54,960
What did you eat? You've lost weight.

30
00:01:54,960 --> 00:01:58,140
You must not have eaten well in our hometown. Eat more later.

31
00:01:58,140 --> 00:02:00,760
- Dinner is almost ready.
- Thanks, Uncle Ding.

32
00:02:00,760 --> 00:02:02,080
You're welcome.

33
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:03,859
I don't think I've lost weight.

34
00:02:03,859 --> 00:02:05,959
Let me look at you.

35
00:02:08,139 --> 00:02:09,819
Come on, Xile, eat more.

36
00:02:09,819 --> 00:02:12,160
- Thank you, Uncle Ding.
- Have a piece of meat.

37
00:02:12,160 --> 00:02:13,840
It's so delicious.

38
00:02:13,840 --> 00:02:16,860
That's your Uncle Ding's cooking.

39
00:02:19,219 --> 00:02:23,200
Baobei, look, daughters are the best, right?

40
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:25,600
Daughters know how to surprise you by coming home unexpectedly.

41
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:29,000
This kind of thing would never happen with Ding Ran.

42
00:02:30,359 --> 00:02:34,300
By the way, how did you get along with Ran?

43
00:02:35,439 --> 00:02:38,320
He was out early and back late, out late and back at dawn.

44
00:02:38,320 --> 00:02:40,679
I had no time to get along with him.

45
00:02:45,399 --> 00:02:48,499
It's okay. Don't mind him. Let's eat.

46
00:02:48,499 --> 00:02:50,020
- Let's eat.
- Here.

47
00:02:50,020 --> 00:02:52,100
Thank you, Uncle Ding.

48
00:02:53,560 --> 00:02:56,999
- Xiao Ke, I'm back.
- Liuliu.

49
00:02:58,660 --> 00:03:01,099
Liuliu, you're back.

50
00:03:01,999 --> 00:03:04,419
How did you know I was back?

51
00:03:04,419 --> 00:03:06,820
Jiang Xile told me you would come to the store today.

52
00:03:06,820 --> 00:03:09,240
Yes, I have to come to the store early.

53
00:03:09,240 --> 00:03:12,300
Otherwise, I'll be accused of having no plans for the future again.

54
00:03:12,300 --> 00:03:14,820
He has to find ways to send me money.

55
00:03:14,820 --> 00:03:17,480
Liuliu, I'm sorry.

56
00:03:17,480 --> 00:03:19,939
I was wrong.

57
00:03:19,939 --> 00:03:25,020
I always did what I wanted to do without considering your feelings.

58
00:03:25,020 --> 00:03:27,459
Look, I've returned the clothes I bought from you.

59
00:03:27,459 --> 00:03:29,980
Can you give me the money back?

60
00:03:31,660 --> 00:03:33,780
Qi Fei, is there something wrong with you?

61
00:03:33,780 --> 00:03:36,879
Is your thought process always this unique for everything you do?

62
00:03:36,879 --> 00:03:38,300
Is there something wrong?

63
00:03:38,300 --> 00:03:41,480
Today, I helped you sell two pieces of clothes and a pair of shoes.

64
00:03:47,139 --> 00:03:49,880
Would you like to go upstairs for tea?

65
00:03:51,399 --> 00:03:53,599
Have tea again? Today, I—

66
00:03:53,599 --> 00:03:56,319
It's really just tea.

67
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:31,920
Why didn't you tell me before you left?

68
00:04:37,879 --> 00:04:40,999
I sent Jiang Jiang to my fourth aunt-in-law's house.

69
00:04:41,680 --> 00:04:44,080
Didn't even leave me a dog.

70
00:05:02,740 --> 00:05:04,619
Is it too late?

71
00:05:13,900 --> 00:05:16,299
I'll be back in a week.
[Ding Ran]

72
00:05:55,080 --> 00:05:56,460
Here.

73
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:59,559
You really look the part.

74
00:05:59,559 --> 00:06:02,100
Are you really sure about opening this cafe?

75
00:06:02,100 --> 00:06:05,280
Of course, I'm sure. This cafe used to belong to my cousin.

76
00:06:05,280 --> 00:06:09,300
She's now a high-ranking executive at a company. She's busy every day. So she sold it to me.

77
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:12,860
Trust me, the business at this cafe will definitely not be bad.

78
00:06:12,860 --> 00:06:14,780
Besides, it's close to your store.

79
00:06:14,780 --> 00:06:17,799
We can meet anytime we want to meet.

80
00:06:17,799 --> 00:06:21,280
- You won't get tired of it?
- How can I get tired of it?

81
00:06:23,879 --> 00:06:27,320
Motorcycle, skateboard, coffee, and cake.

82
00:06:27,320 --> 00:06:31,680
As long as it's something you want to do, every single thing can be done well.

83
00:06:32,399 --> 00:06:34,360
Not like me.

84
00:06:35,459 --> 00:06:39,739
Liuliu, I don't mean anything else.

85
00:06:39,739 --> 00:06:44,120
I brought you here just to share my joy with you.

86
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:46,520
I want you to understand me more.

87
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,380
I don't mean anything else, either.

88
00:06:48,380 --> 00:06:53,020
I just think now dating is also pretty good.

89
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:54,839
Really?

90
00:06:54,839 --> 00:06:57,259
Why?

91
00:06:57,259 --> 00:07:01,440
Because the person I'm dating is you.

92
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:08,968
Be careful, it's hot.

93
00:07:11,740 --> 00:07:13,880
Okay, I've already had the coffee.

94
00:07:13,880 --> 00:07:17,160
Now I have to go back and plan our grand scheme with Jiang Xile.

95
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:20,500
- What grand scheme?
- Bye.

96
00:07:20,500 --> 00:07:21,620
Liuliu.

97
00:07:21,620 --> 00:07:25,260
My need is comfort. Your need is…

98
00:07:25,260 --> 00:07:27,840
Sexy, good-looking, comfortable.

99
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:31,179
Like this kind of underwear, although it's comfortable, it's not good-looking.

100
00:07:31,179 --> 00:07:33,399
Anyway, I wouldn't choose this kind.

101
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:35,899
The underwear we have to make has to be all-round.

102
00:07:35,899 --> 00:07:41,100
That's right. Good-looking underwear can also be paired with other clothes in our store.

103
00:07:41,100 --> 00:07:43,440
- Kill two birds with one stone.
- What are we waiting for?

104
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:44,859
Let's get started.

105
00:07:44,859 --> 00:07:46,660
Let's get started.

106
00:08:37,800 --> 00:08:40,260
Welcome.

107
00:08:42,039 --> 00:08:44,380
It's so late, but you said welcome.

108
00:08:44,959 --> 00:08:46,839
Your delivery is here.

109
00:08:52,279 --> 00:08:55,000
How is it? Is this flavor suitable for you?

110
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,000
Do you want me to buy something else?

111
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:59,540
No need. It's delicious.

112
00:09:01,299 --> 00:09:04,479
Aren't you supposed to come back in two more days?

113
00:09:04,479 --> 00:09:07,000
Are you counting the days for when I'll be back?

114
00:09:07,000 --> 00:09:10,100
Don't flatter yourself. I didn't.

115
00:09:10,100 --> 00:09:11,699
Okay.

116
00:09:12,560 --> 00:09:16,560
It's so late. Is it just you in the store? Where is Liuliu?

117
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:19,819
Liuliu is tired. She's asleep upstairs.

118
00:09:19,819 --> 00:09:23,780
I have some work to do in a while. You can go back now.

119
00:09:25,580 --> 00:09:29,699
I see you're quite tired, too. Shall I tell you a joke?

120
00:09:29,699 --> 00:09:31,660
What joke?

121
00:09:32,839 --> 00:09:37,979
A long, long time ago, there was a big bear and a little white rabbit in the forest. They went to the toilet together.

122
00:09:37,979 --> 00:09:41,280
The big bear asked the little white rabbit, "Are you afraid of getting dirty?"

123
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:43,879
The little white rabbit said no.

124
00:09:43,879 --> 00:09:47,040
Then the big bear asked the little white rabbit, "Do you lose fur?"

125
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:50,700
The little white rabbit said no. Then—

126
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:57,880
Then the big bear grabbed the little white rabbit and wiped his butt.

127
00:09:57,880 --> 00:10:02,080
Isn't this the joke I told you before? How do you still remember?

128
00:10:02,080 --> 00:10:07,139
At that time, you told me five stories about the little white rabbit. I remember every one of them.

129
00:10:20,279 --> 00:10:23,219
It seems like the air conditioning is a bit cold.

130
00:10:23,219 --> 00:10:27,180
I'll go put a coat on Liuliu.

131
00:10:30,159 --> 00:10:31,859
Jiang Xile.

132
00:10:32,879 --> 00:10:38,480
Can the little white rabbit start a new life with the big bear?

133
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:53,520
I don't know how they can start a new life now.

134
00:11:20,540 --> 00:11:23,240
Baby, you're up.

135
00:11:23,919 --> 00:11:25,500
Where did these flowers come from?

136
00:11:25,500 --> 00:11:28,099
Of course, they were given to me by your Uncle Ding.

137
00:11:28,099 --> 00:11:31,620
What's the occasion today? Why give flowers?

138
00:11:31,620 --> 00:11:35,239
Yes, I also asked him, "What's the occasion for giving flowers today?"

139
00:11:35,239 --> 00:11:39,459
He said he just passed by a flower shop on the way back and he wanted to give them to me.

140
00:11:39,459 --> 00:11:41,420
Romantic, right?

141
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:49,856
Mom.

142
00:11:50,820 --> 00:11:56,300
Dad has been gone for so many years. You've been resisting getting remarry.

143
00:11:56,300 --> 00:12:01,200
Uncle Ding also told me when you two just reunited, you refused him.

144
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:03,659
Why did you accept him later?

145
00:12:04,479 --> 00:12:07,900
Actually, I am a very sensitive woman.

146
00:12:07,900 --> 00:12:12,319
I'm afraid of people gossiping behind my back.

147
00:12:16,219 --> 00:12:19,300
But your Uncle Ding gives me a sense of security.

148
00:12:19,300 --> 00:12:23,840
Everything he does can eliminate my inner worries.

149
00:12:33,339 --> 00:12:34,860
I see.

150
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:39,920
Baby, actually, career and love are the same.

151
00:12:39,920 --> 00:12:45,240
It doesn't matter if they're late. As long as they appear, that's the best time.

152
00:12:45,240 --> 00:12:49,159
So no matter what you do, I will always support you.

153
00:12:49,159 --> 00:12:50,959
Keep going.

154
00:12:50,959 --> 00:12:52,880
Thank you, Ms. Xiao Baobei.

155
00:12:52,880 --> 00:12:54,719
You're so nice.

156
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:58,119
Of course.

157
00:12:58,119 --> 00:13:00,760
It's about time. Let's go help Uncle Ding cook.

158
00:13:00,760 --> 00:13:03,640
You can't cook at all. You just arrange flowers.

159
00:13:03,640 --> 00:13:05,352
I'll go.

160
00:13:13,720 --> 00:13:17,040
Xile, I really didn't see it. You can cook.

161
00:13:17,040 --> 00:13:20,119
Uncle Ding, I was forced to learn how to cook.

162
00:13:20,119 --> 00:13:25,060
After all, you must know the taste of my mom's cooking.

163
00:13:25,060 --> 00:13:26,800
It's okay, I can swallow it.

164
00:13:26,800 --> 00:13:29,840
When I was little, I couldn't swallow it at all.

165
00:13:29,840 --> 00:13:33,280
Don't let your mom hear this.

166
00:13:41,379 --> 00:13:44,280
Uncle Ding, do you have vinegar?

167
00:13:44,280 --> 00:13:47,339
Check the cabinet under the microwave. There should be a new bottle.

168
00:13:47,339 --> 00:13:48,872
Okay.

169
00:14:04,999 --> 00:14:08,759
Dad, there's no vinegar, only soy sauce.

170
00:14:08,759 --> 00:14:11,280
- No vinegar?
- No.

171
00:14:13,079 --> 00:14:15,839
I remember there was a new bottle.

172
00:14:17,100 --> 00:14:18,960
- I'll go buy it.
- Never mind.

173
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:21,700
You just got back. Take a rest. I'll go.

174
00:14:28,760 --> 00:14:31,959
Aren't you working the morning shift today?

175
00:14:33,720 --> 00:14:37,340
Looks like you really care about me. You know what shift I work every day.

176
00:14:37,340 --> 00:14:39,380
I can't be bothered to care about you.

177
00:14:39,380 --> 00:14:42,899
I just happened to hear your dad talking to my mom.

178
00:14:43,760 --> 00:14:45,600
Your mom and my dad are really…

179
00:14:45,600 --> 00:14:49,320
They are not married yet, but they act like an old married couple.

180
00:14:58,059 --> 00:14:59,584
- Ding Ran.
- Yes.

181
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:04,220
Let's just be a simple family like this.

182
00:15:07,919 --> 00:15:09,560
What do you mean?

183
00:15:09,560 --> 00:15:14,319
We can't date because we're about to become siblings.

184
00:15:15,279 --> 00:15:17,700
Who wants to be your sibling?

185
00:15:19,039 --> 00:15:23,100
Is it because our parents are lovers that you don't want to be in a relationship with me?

186
00:15:25,279 --> 00:15:27,980
If our parents remarry, we're family.

187
00:15:27,980 --> 00:15:31,880
If we're lovers, we're also family. What's the difference?

188
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:35,020
That's exactly it. Parents get married.

189
00:15:35,020 --> 00:15:38,100
Son and daughter are in a relationship. What a mess of a relationship.

190
00:15:38,100 --> 00:15:40,020
It's a relationship of love.

191
00:15:40,020 --> 00:15:42,160
Others won't see it that way.

192
00:15:44,359 --> 00:15:47,800
Jiang Xile, what does this have to do with other people?

193
00:15:47,800 --> 00:15:49,919
I don't accept this reason.

194
00:15:50,879 --> 00:15:52,819
Well, I don't like you.

195
00:15:52,819 --> 00:15:55,600
I can't date you. Is this reason good enough?

196
00:15:55,600 --> 00:15:57,139
I don't believe this reason.

197
00:15:57,139 --> 00:15:59,020
Believe it or not.

198
00:16:00,201 --> 00:16:04,360
♫ So don't worry too much about it ♫

199
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:06,040
Jiang Xile.

200
00:16:07,480 --> 00:16:11,900
You need to make things clear to me. I don't accept this explanation.

201
00:16:13,360 --> 00:16:15,560
Let go of me, Ding Ran.

202
00:16:17,540 --> 00:16:20,390
♫ Doing things the wrong way can be very hurtful ♫

203
00:16:20,390 --> 00:16:25,280
Once I get ahold on something, I'll never let go.

204
00:16:26,007 --> 00:16:30,990
♫ I will not be sorry to leave you in the old place ♫

205
00:16:34,079 --> 00:16:35,692
Ding Ran.

206
00:16:36,580 --> 00:16:38,380
Ding Ran.

207
00:16:38,380 --> 00:16:40,160
Jiang Xile, why are you stepping on me?

208
00:16:40,160 --> 00:16:42,700
Why am I stepping on you? Have you watched too many TV dramas?

209
00:16:42,700 --> 00:16:45,020
What's our relationship? Why are you being so indecent?

210
00:16:45,020 --> 00:16:48,720
I... I'm not being indecent.

211
00:16:48,720 --> 00:16:53,259
When I see the person I like, naturally, I want to kiss her.

212
00:16:55,500 --> 00:16:58,119
When I see someone I hate, of course I want to beat him.

213
00:16:58,119 --> 00:16:59,620
Calm down.

214
00:16:59,620 --> 00:17:02,979
- Calm down, calm down. Being with me, I didn't...
- You can rest assured. They've been getting along recently.

215
00:17:02,979 --> 00:17:04,740
- Ding Ran.
- Calm down.

216
00:17:04,740 --> 00:17:06,220
You stand still.

217
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:09,120
Slow down. Wait. Calm down.

218
00:17:09,120 --> 00:17:11,220
What, calm down? What's our relationship?

219
00:17:11,220 --> 00:17:12,779
Come here.

220
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,359
Are you sure they're getting along well?

221
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:18,760
- For real. Wait.
- What weapon is Xile using again?

222
00:17:18,760 --> 00:17:21,340
Stand still! Stand there.

223
00:17:35,780 --> 00:17:39,180
Say, who are they messaging?

224
00:17:39,180 --> 00:17:44,820
Usually, at this time, they're cursing each other with their friends.

225
00:17:53,199 --> 00:17:55,839
Why do you always avoid me?

226
00:17:59,039 --> 00:18:03,000
Nonsense. I don't like you.

227
00:18:03,780 --> 00:18:06,939
Then from today, try to like me.

228
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:10,099
I can't try.

229
00:18:10,099 --> 00:18:12,879
I won't give up.

230
00:18:12,879 --> 00:18:15,239
I won't surrender.

231
00:18:19,440 --> 00:18:23,519
Xile, good morning. I've prepared soy milk and sandwiches for you.

232
00:18:23,519 --> 00:18:24,880
Give them a try.

233
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:27,059
I don't eat breakfast.

234
00:18:35,239 --> 00:18:37,440
Ding Ran asked me to give it to you.

235
00:18:50,219 --> 00:18:52,120
What's this?

236
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:54,259
I knew you would pop it.

237
00:18:54,259 --> 00:18:58,220
Jiang Xile, I want to date you badly.

238
00:18:58,220 --> 00:19:00,999
Can we watch a play together tomorrow?

239
00:19:03,940 --> 00:19:06,420
What are you looking at?

240
00:19:07,919 --> 00:19:10,159
Is it cool or not?

241
00:19:10,159 --> 00:19:11,700
What's cool or not?

242
00:19:11,700 --> 00:19:15,619
Fortune turns. In ten years, he is now the one pestering you.

243
00:19:15,619 --> 00:19:18,059
Tell me. Is it cool or not?

244
00:19:18,059 --> 00:19:19,939
Cool or not? Cool or not?

245
00:19:19,939 --> 00:19:21,720
Cool, cool.

246
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:23,899
You'll feel very cool.

247
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:31,000
Let me help you.

248
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,120
Stay away from me.

249
00:19:33,879 --> 00:19:37,379
We're a family. How can I stay far away from you?

250
00:19:38,780 --> 00:19:40,639
Give me your hands.

251
00:19:45,019 --> 00:19:47,680
Uncle Ding, Ding Ran is pinching me.

252
00:19:47,680 --> 00:19:49,820
- He is pinching me.
- No, Jiang Xile, you, you…

253
00:19:49,820 --> 00:19:51,400
Dad, Dad, no.

254
00:19:51,400 --> 00:19:53,540
- Why do you do this every day? Stand still.
- No.

255
00:19:53,540 --> 00:19:55,899
- Listen to my explanation, Dad.
- Stand still!

256
00:20:05,300 --> 00:20:08,200
Don't ask anymore. I won't agree.

257
00:20:08,200 --> 00:20:11,000
I called to tell you something else.

258
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,100
What?

259
00:20:14,100 --> 00:20:17,400
Nothing. I'll hang up.

260
00:20:24,800 --> 00:20:28,900
This line sounds so familiar.

261
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,000
Fried egg with a runny yolk. Sugar-free soy milk.

262
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,100
Whole wheat bread.

263
00:20:35,100 --> 00:20:37,500
Uncle Ding, I'm picky about food.

264
00:20:37,500 --> 00:20:40,100
You don't have to prepare so much for me.

265
00:20:40,100 --> 00:20:43,000
Aren't you and my Mom going on a trip? Hurry up and just go.

266
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:46,600
Preparing food for you is the happiest thing for me.

267
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:49,400
By the way,

268
00:20:50,200 --> 00:20:52,400
I have a good thing for you.

269
00:20:55,200 --> 00:20:57,800
- Chewing gum?
- This is not chewing gum.

270
00:20:57,800 --> 00:20:59,500
Look.

271
00:21:01,700 --> 00:21:05,300
Cockroach. The thing Ding Ran is most afraid of in his life is cockroaches.

272
00:21:05,300 --> 00:21:08,400
These few days when your Mom and I are away, if he bullies you again,

273
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:11,500
put this in his drawer and scare him.

274
00:21:11,500 --> 00:21:14,400
- Thank you, Uncle Ding.
- Go for it.

275
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,800
Go for it.

276
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:18,400
Okay, I'll go see how your Mom is packing.

277
00:21:18,400 --> 00:21:20,000
Eat.

278
00:21:37,700 --> 00:21:39,700
Not quite right.

279
00:21:42,500 --> 00:21:44,100
No good.

280
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:56,500
[Jiang Xile and Ding Ran's Ten-Year Plan]

281
00:21:58,630 --> 00:22:00,410
[Jiang Xile and Ding Ran's Ten-Year Plan]

282
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:11,200
[Red really suits you]

283
00:22:11,200 --> 00:22:15,580
♫ As darkness falls in the sky, the road appears short, and destiny changes ♫

284
00:22:15,580 --> 00:22:19,200
♫ Who can escape judgment by spinning lies? ♫

285
00:22:19,200 --> 00:22:22,600
[If my confession is successful, today will be the first Spring Festival after falling in love.]

286
00:22:22,600 --> 00:22:25,400
♫ How do we reconcile? ♫

287
00:22:25,400 --> 00:22:31,200
[I like mountains, forests, and rivers. Let's go together]

288
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:35,100
♫ There are always some answers that will never be revealed ♫

289
00:22:35,100 --> 00:22:37,200
[If my confession is successful, I should propose today.]

290
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:41,300
[Wedding Date]

291
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:48,700
♫ Saying, "I like you," comes too late ♫

292
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:52,100
♫ Thinking back to when we first met ♫

293
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:57,100
♫ I had sweaty palms and my senses awestruck ♫

294
00:22:57,100 --> 00:23:02,900
[If my confession was successful, today wouldn't be this kind of encounter.]

295
00:23:02,900 --> 00:23:05,800
♫ All at once, overnight, I realized I had loved you deeply then ♫

296
00:23:05,800 --> 00:23:10,100
♫ All at once, overnight, I realized I had loved you deeply then ♫

297
00:23:11,600 --> 00:23:13,100
Hello, Qi Fei.

298
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:16,800
Jiang Xile, come over quickly. Ding Ran had an accident.

299
00:23:19,700 --> 00:23:22,400
- Ding Ran.
- Welcome.

300
00:23:22,400 --> 00:23:25,100
Qi Fei, what's the matter?

301
00:23:25,100 --> 00:23:27,700
I've told you not to tell her.

302
00:23:27,700 --> 00:23:30,200
You were knocked unconscious, but you still don't want me to tell her.

303
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,400
Knocked unconscious?

304
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:35,400
Aren't you a doctor? How could you let yourself get like this?

305
00:23:35,400 --> 00:23:38,600
I can't do it. I feel dizzy.

306
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:41,500
Jiang Xile, you should send him home quickly.

307
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:43,300
Okay, let's go, Ding Ran.

308
00:23:43,300 --> 00:23:46,000
Be careful, take it slow.

309
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:47,200
Slow down. Slow down.

310
00:23:47,200 --> 00:23:48,900
Slow down.

311
00:23:50,300 --> 00:23:51,900
- Rest assured.
- Slow down.

312
00:23:51,900 --> 00:23:54,000
Slow down, Ding Ran.

313
00:23:56,300 --> 00:23:58,700
- Be careful.
- I feel dizzy.

314
00:24:04,200 --> 00:24:06,300
You sit on the couch for a bit.

315
00:24:06,300 --> 00:24:07,800
Come.

316
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,700
What happened?

317
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:17,600
Well, I was in Qi Fei's cafe today.

318
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:21,400
I saw a little cat.

319
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:25,800
It kept running on the beam.

320
00:24:25,800 --> 00:24:30,800
Then, as it was running, it knocked over a flower pot.

321
00:24:30,800 --> 00:24:32,900
It hit me.

322
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:36,600
Then, I fainted.

323
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:39,500
Is it so serious?

324
00:24:39,500 --> 00:24:41,200
Let me see.

325
00:24:41,800 --> 00:24:43,800
It hurts a bit.

326
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:46,900
Rest for a bit.

327
00:24:47,800 --> 00:24:51,500
It's so serious. Didn't the hospital give you any medicine?

328
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:54,500
Medicine.

329
00:24:54,500 --> 00:24:58,400
Medicine. I left my medicine at Qi Fei's cafe.

330
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:01,200
I will go find your medicine box first.

331
00:25:01,200 --> 00:25:02,800
No need.

332
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:08,000
Just let me lean on you.

333
00:25:19,600 --> 00:25:21,600
Let me see the wound.

334
00:25:23,600 --> 00:25:27,400
It was a plastic flower pot. It didn't cause much damage.

335
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:29,000
Still, let me check.

336
00:25:29,000 --> 00:25:34,000
If it's serious, I need to call an ambulance for you.

337
00:25:39,300 --> 00:25:41,500
Too dizzy.

338
00:25:41,500 --> 00:25:43,600
Too dizzy, too dizzy…

339
00:25:45,500 --> 00:25:47,500
So dizzy.

340
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:52,400
Ding Ran, stop pretending. Get up.

341
00:25:54,900 --> 00:25:56,500
Get up.

342
00:26:04,400 --> 00:26:07,000
If you want to pretend, keep pretending.

343
00:26:08,200 --> 00:26:10,700
I have some words to say to you.

344
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:16,600
Ding Ran, I really, really like you.

345
00:26:16,600 --> 00:26:20,600
I liked you in the past, and I like you now.

346
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:27,700
Back at our hometown, the first time you said you liked me,

347
00:26:27,700 --> 00:26:30,200
I couldn't sleep all night.

348
00:26:30,200 --> 00:26:32,700
I always thought you were joking.

349
00:26:32,700 --> 00:26:37,400
How could something like you liking me possibly happen to me?

350
00:26:39,200 --> 00:26:42,300
The second time you asked me if it was too late.

351
00:26:43,050 --> 00:26:47,000
♫ You ignored that sleep talk-like monologue ♫

352
00:26:47,000 --> 00:26:49,300
I felt a bit wronged.

353
00:26:50,600 --> 00:26:55,800
You said those coincidences I thought about were all encounters you had planned.

354
00:26:55,800 --> 00:27:00,500
But Ding Ran, I want you to be clear

355
00:27:01,200 --> 00:27:04,100
those like you didn't express.

356
00:27:04,100 --> 00:27:07,500
I just couldn't feel them.

357
00:27:09,760 --> 00:27:13,600
♫ Endless like sailing, not afraid of being blown away by the wind ♫

358
00:27:13,600 --> 00:27:15,400
I'm sorry.

359
00:27:17,000 --> 00:27:19,100
I should have said it all.

360
00:27:19,100 --> 00:27:20,800
Forget it.

361
00:27:22,600 --> 00:27:25,500
Jiang Xile, don't go.

362
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:33,700
♫ I wait for you to give me your embrace in the mundane world ♫

363
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:36,000
After we came back,

364
00:27:36,000 --> 00:27:41,600
you kept asking me when we could be in a relationship.

365
00:27:42,500 --> 00:27:45,400
I felt even more wronged.

366
00:27:45,400 --> 00:27:48,100
I thought, "Why?"

367
00:27:48,100 --> 00:27:52,300
When I liked you so much before, you were indifferent.

368
00:27:52,300 --> 00:27:56,100
Now you say you like me and I have to agree.

369
00:27:56,100 --> 00:27:59,500
I have self-respect too.

370
00:28:00,700 --> 00:28:03,800
Xile, I was wrong.

371
00:28:03,800 --> 00:28:07,800
It was my unclear expressions before, my dilly-dallying plan,

372
00:28:07,800 --> 00:28:13,100
and my boring self-respect that wasted a whole ten years.

373
00:28:14,300 --> 00:28:16,500
I was really wrong.

374
00:28:16,500 --> 00:28:18,500
I'm sorry.

375
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:20,700
Will you forgive me?

376
00:28:34,200 --> 00:28:38,100
♫ You are the love that's out of reach ♫

377
00:28:38,100 --> 00:28:42,300
Then give me a reason. Why should I be in a relationship with you?

378
00:28:42,300 --> 00:28:47,000
Jiang Xile, I really like you.

379
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:49,200
Can we date?

380
00:28:49,900 --> 00:28:51,500
No.

381
00:28:51,500 --> 00:28:55,200
I only like you, from the past, now, to the future.

382
00:28:55,200 --> 00:28:57,300
Can we date?

383
00:28:57,300 --> 00:28:59,200
No.

384
00:29:03,300 --> 00:29:08,000
Jiang Xile, I want to date you badly.

385
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:12,400
So badly that I want to date you for a lifetime.

386
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:15,200
Can we date?

387
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:19,000
No.

388
00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:23,800
Still no?

389
00:29:23,800 --> 00:29:25,400
Why?

390
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:28,500
Because Lu Liulu bet with me.

391
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:33,840
If I love you again, I have to lose 8,888 yuan to her.

392
00:29:33,840 --> 00:29:36,600
♫ Flipping through the pages of our story ♫

393
00:29:36,600 --> 00:29:39,300
♫ Even if the sea in the palm of my hand is empty, I will not let go ♫

394
00:29:39,300 --> 00:29:41,040
What are you doing?

395
00:29:41,040 --> 00:29:46,300
[Flocade]
♫ Even if the sea in the palm of my hand is empty, I will not let go ♫

396
00:29:46,300 --> 00:29:47,700
How is it?

397
00:29:47,700 --> 00:29:49,900
Looks a bit ugly.

398
00:29:49,900 --> 00:29:51,500
But it tastes quite good!

399
00:29:51,500 --> 00:29:53,700
Qi Fei, you really can't talk.

400
00:29:53,700 --> 00:29:56,100
What's wrong?

401
00:29:56,100 --> 00:29:58,100
Message, message.

402
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:04,300
[Money Transfer]

403
00:30:05,300 --> 00:30:07,300
What's wrong?

404
00:30:07,300 --> 00:30:10,300
Why did Ding Ran suddenly transfer money to me?

405
00:30:10,300 --> 00:30:12,300
Does he owe you money?

406
00:30:15,800 --> 00:30:17,500
Not owing me money.

407
00:30:17,500 --> 00:30:21,800
It's the love debt he owed Jiang Xile finally repaid.

408
00:30:21,800 --> 00:30:23,700
I helped you pay it back.

409
00:30:23,700 --> 00:30:26,700
Why did you let her make a profit?

410
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:42,900
'Those Years' - Liu Yixin

411
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:50,600
♫ Page by page, the photos look more like full stops  ♫

412
00:30:50,600 --> 00:30:58,100
♫ I'm alone in my room, reminiscing about the past ♫

413
00:30:58,100 --> 00:31:05,700
♫ No matter how far the lens of memory can reach, it will eventually lose focus ♫

414
00:31:05,700 --> 00:31:15,300
♫ It is a natural part of life for adults to come and go ♫

415
00:31:15,300 --> 00:31:19,000
♫ All these years, we cried and laughed are memories we cherished ♫

416
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:21,400
♫ All these years, we cried and laughed are memories we cherished ♫

417
00:31:21,400 --> 00:31:26,600
♫ In a blink of an eye, time encourages change ♫

418
00:31:26,600 --> 00:31:30,500
♫ A heart shattered in regrets is hard to mend ♫

419
00:31:30,500 --> 00:31:34,900
♫ It may take several more years to forget those years ♫

420
00:31:34,900 --> 00:31:38,700
♫ My willingness to be cute is not simple ♫
